===Etymology===
Probably from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|-}}, though the exact etymon is unclear. Compare {{cog|bo|གཡའ||to itch}}, {{cog|kac|kaya||to itch}}, {{cog|my|ယား||to itch}}, {{cog|sit-jap|rɤʑa||to itch}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2017}}; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques and Lai, 2019}}), which STEDT (under the entry *g-ya) derives from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ja||to itch}}. Also compare {{cog|lep|ᰚᰭ|tr=yak|t=to itch}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), which STEDT derives from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m-sak||to itch}}.

